Here is the implementation for TextReader using javascript and React Native. This code uses react-native-tts which is a text-to-speech interface for React Native.

First, we will need to install `react-native-tts` using npm or yarn. Here is how to do it:

```bash
npm install react-native-tts
# or
yarn add react-native-tts
```

Now let's implement the TextReader component.

```javascript
// import the necessary modules
import React, { Component } from 'react';
import { Text, StyleSheet, View, TouchableOpacity } from 'react-native';
import Tts from 'react-native-tts';

// define the TextReader component
export default class TextReader extends Component {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props);
    this.state = { ttsStatus: "stopped" };
  }

  // method to control the text-to-speech feature
  readText = async (text) => {
    await Tts.speak(text);
    this.setState({ ttsStatus: "started" });
  }

  // when the component is about to unmount, stop the Tts
  componentWillUnmount() {
    if(this.state.ttsStatus == "started") {
       Tts.stop();
    }
  }

  // render the component on the screen
  render() {
    // get text from props
    const { text } = this.props;

    return (
      <View style={styles.container}>
        <Text style={styles.text}>{text}</Text>
        <TouchableOpacity
          style={styles.button}
          onPress={() => this.readText(text)}
        >
          <Text style={styles.buttonText}>Read Text</Text>
        </TouchableOpacity>
      </View>
    );
  }
}

// define the styles
const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    flex: 1,
    justifyContent: 'center',
    alignItems: 'center',
    backgroundColor: '#f5fcff',
  },
  text: {
    fontSize: 20,
    textAlign: 'center',
    margin: 10,
  },
  button: {
    backgroundColor: '#841584',
    padding: 10
  },
  buttonText: {
    color: 'white'
  }
});
```

In this code, we first import all the necessary modules. The TextReader component class is created with state variable `ttsStatus` that controls if the text-to-speech feature is running or not. The `readText` method is invoked when the 'Read Text' button is pressed. It uses the `Tts.speak(text)` method from react-native-tts module to read the text aloud. When the TextReader component is about to unmount, the `Tts.stop()` method is called to stop the text-to-speech. The rendered view of the component contains a `Text` to display the text and a `TouchableOpacity` used as a button to initiate the text-to-speech feature.
